[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A clinical trial recruitment conversationalist decomposes into eleven logical stages: trial-content authoring with IRB-approved corpus management, trial-state and amendment tracking, recruitment-cohort enrollment with referral-source attribution, channel entry, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-trial-context loading, conversation handling with strict citation-grounding, eligibility-evaluation with deterministic per-criterion logic, output safety screening with IRB-approved-content faithfulness verification, coordinator-handoff orchestration, and per-trial audit and representativeness reporting. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.9 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (IRB-approved-corpus-as-only-permitted-source, eligibility-evaluation rule engine with deterministic per-criterion logic and clinical-leadership ownership, trial-state machine with amendment tracking, coordinator-handoff orchestration as production scope, and per-trial-and-per-cohort recruitment-funnel instrumentation).
