[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the clinical-trial recruitment conversationalist.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IRB-approved-corpus-as-only-permitted-source for trial-specific content.** The architecture does not permit the LLM to generate novel trial-specific recruitment language. The corpus is the source. The LLM retrieves and surfaces; it does not author. The output-safety verifier detects novel-recruitment-language and regenerates or falls back. This discipline is not optional, it is the architectural floor.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Eligibility-evaluation rule engine with named clinical-leadership ownership per criterion.** Each criterion has named clinical-leadership ownership (the principal investigator, a designated sub-investigator, or a clinical-research-leadership team member depending on the criterion), version history, and IRB-review evidence per version. The LLM does not interpret criteria; the rule engine does.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Trial-state machine with amendment tracking.** Trials open and close, sites enroll or not, IRB amendments are approved or not. The trial-state system is the source of truth for whether any given conversation is permissible. Conversations about closed-or-paused trials route appropriately rather than continuing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordinator-handoff orchestration as production scope.** The handoff is not "send the coordinator an email." It is a structured package with tagged patient-reported information, eligibility-evaluation result, patient-stated topics of interest, preferred follow-up logistics, and trial-context, delivered to the coordinator-team queue with capacity-aware routing. The coordinator team is a co-design partner from the start.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-trial-and-per-cohort recruitment-funnel instrumentation.** The recruitment funnel is instrumented per trial, per demographic stratum, per referral source, per channel. Diversity-action-plan stratum-level monitoring is not a "nice to have" for FDA-regulated trials; it is regulatory expectation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous emergency screening across every utterance.** Same as the previous bots in this chapter. The assistant routes acute emergencies immediately to the triage pathway, the mental-health pathway, or 911 as appropriate; the assistant does not try to handle acute emergencies in conversation. Recruitment is paused when a safety event is in scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every trial-specific assertion cites its IRB-approved-content source with version. Every eligibility-evaluation assertion cites its criterion-rule with version. The audit record preserves the citation trail so an IRB or sponsor inspection can reconstruct exactly which IRB-approved content was surfaced when.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Vulnerable-population identity model.** The identity layer distinguishes adult-self-decision, parental-permission-and-pediatric-assent, and surrogate-decision-maker scenarios. Where the trial enrolls a population with additional federal protections, the additional protections are operationalized.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Research-data-as-distinct-record-class.** Recruitment-conversation content is research data, retained per the IRB-approved data-retention plan, with access controls per the institutional research-data-access policy, and an audit trail that supports IRB and regulatory inspection.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the trial-corpus retrieval, the eligibility rule engine, the trial-state system, the coordinator-queue routing, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble pulling that information right now; if you'd like, I can connect you to a research coordinator who can help." The graceful-degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
