I'll append content to file: [38;5;141mchapter11.10-clinical-trial-recruitment-conversationalist.md[0m[38;5;244m (using tool: write)[0m
Purpose: Append Why These Services and Architecture Diagram

[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The AWS Implementation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Why These Services
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Bedrock for the LLM and embeddings.** Same selection criteria as recipes 11.1 through 11.9. The recruitment conversationalist specifically benefits from a model with strong instruction-following for strict citation grounding (the LLM must not produce novel trial-specific language), strong tool-use for orchestrating retrieval and eligibility evaluation, and good multilingual support for the diverse populations recruitment platforms reach. Claude Sonnet-class models or comparable frontier models for orchestration; smaller models for intent classification and routine summarization. Bedrock is HIPAA-eligible under BAA. The recruitment conversation's hard constraint on novel-language production places a premium on instruction-following discipline, and the citation-grounding pattern is an explicit selection criterion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Bedrock Knowledge Bases for the IRB-approved trial corpus.** Per-trial knowledge bases (or per-trial namespaces within a knowledge base, depending on the deployment scale) hold the IRB-approved protocol summary, FAQ entries, visit-schedule summary, study-procedure summary, disclosures, and disqualified-participant communication, indexed for retrieval. Metadata-filtered retrieval per trial, per content-type, per language, and per version is the architectural primitive. Knowledge Bases provides the managed RAG layer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Bedrock Agents for tool orchestration.** Same selection rationale as recipes 11.2 through 11.9. The recruitment-conversationalist tools (trial_protocol_summary_retrieve, trial_faq_retrieve, trial_visit_schedule_retrieve, trial_study_procedures_retrieve, eligibility_criterion_evaluate, prescreen_capture, prescreen_summary_compose, coordinator_handoff_schedule, trial_state_retrieve, alternative_trial_propose, escalation_propose, representativeness_capture) are defined as Agents action groups with OpenAPI schemas. The Agent's traces preserve tool-call audit trails for the recruitment-decision-record journal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Bedrock Guardrails for scope and content filtering.** Configured with denied topics including diagnosis-attempted, prescription-attempted, treatment-recommendation-attempted, enroll-or-not-advice-attempted, novel-trial-specific-recruitment-language-attempted, recommendation-pattern (the response crosses from explanation to recommendation), coercion-pattern (the response uses coercive framing), and similar scope violations. The recruitment scope is bounded; Guardrails enforces the boundaries cleanly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon OpenSearch Serverless for the retrieval indices.** The IRB-approved trial corpus across many trials, the eligibility-criterion-rule library, and the recruitment-conversation history all benefit from vector retrieval with metadata filtering. Per-trial namespacing prevents content from one trial leaking into a conversation about another.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS HealthLake for FHIR-native chart-context data, where authenticated patients have an EHR relationship with the institution.** HealthLake provides a managed FHIR data store the assistant queries for Patient, Encounter, Condition, MedicationRequest, MedicationStatement, Observation, DiagnosticReport, AllergyIntolerance, and Immunization resources to inform the prescreen with patient-known information. Where the patient is unauthenticated (sponsor-recruitment channel without EHR linkage), the assistant operates from patient-self-report only with appropriate caveats per the IRB-approved process.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon DynamoDB for state, recruitment-decision-record journal, and trial-state store.** Multiple tables: `trial-corpus-store` (per-trial IRB-approved content with version), `trial-state-store` (open/closed status, site enrollment status, amendment status, recruitment-pause status), `eligibility-criterion-store` (per-trial encoded criteria with rule logic, ownership, version), `recruitment-cohort-store` (per-trial diversity-action-plan stratum targets and progress), `prescreen-store` (per-conversation prescreen results with per-criterion detail), `coordinator-handoff-queue` (per-trial coordinator-routing queue), `conversation-state` (per-conversation transient state), `conversation-metadata` (per-conversation turn-by-turn data), `tool-call-ledger` (audited tool invocations), `recruitment-decision-record-journal` (durable record of recruitment events with citations), and `consent-record` (recruitment-conversation consent posture).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon S3 for the IRB-approved corpus archive, recruitment-conversation archive, recruitment-decision-record journal, and per-trial recruitment-funnel data.** Object Lock in compliance mode for the retention window. Retention sized to the longer of HIPAA's six-year minimum, IRB-approved retention plan, FDA IND or IDE retention obligations (typically 2 years after marketing approval or trial discontinuation, but specific retention varies), and any sponsor or institutional research-data-retention requirements. <!-- TODO: verify; FDA IND record retention requirements are specified in 21 CFR 312.62 and IDE in 21 CFR 812.140; specific retention windows vary -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS Lambda for the conversation handler, eligibility evaluator, trial-state retrieval, coordinator-handoff routing, tool implementations, and recruitment-funnel reporting.** Same pattern as the previous chapter 11 recipes, with additional Lambda functions for each eligibility-criterion evaluator and the recruitment-funnel-reporting workers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon API Gateway and AWS WAF for the public chat endpoint.** Same as the other recipes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon EventBridge for the recruitment-event bus.** Events including patient_entered_recruitment_conversation, prescreen_completed, eligibility_determined, coordinator_handoff_scheduled, vulnerability_flagged, escalation_routed, alternative_trial_suggested, recruitment_decision_recorded, trial_amendment_applied, trial_state_changed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS Step Functions for trial-amendment-driven re-presentation workflows.** When an IRB amendment materially changes recruitment communication, Step Functions orchestrates the re-presentation of updated information to in-flight prospective participants per the IRB-approved process.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Pinpoint for outbound recruitment-channel messaging.** Sponsor-funded campaigns, EHR-prescreen-invitation outreach, and other recruitment-channel messaging delivered via Pinpoint with delivery-status tracking, channel-preference enforcement, and IRB-approved-content discipline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Connect for warm-handoff to research coordinators.** When the assistant escalates or completes a handoff, Connect routes to the appropriate coordinator-team queue with conversation context attached. Coordinators are reachable via Connect's chat and voice queues.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS KMS, AWS Secrets Manager, Amazon CloudWatch, AWS CloudTrail, Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose, AWS Glue, Amazon Athena.** Same operational and audit primitives as the previous recipes, with recruitment-specific KMS key separation for the IRB-approved corpus, the recruitment-decision-record journal, and the prescreen store.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon QuickSight for recruitment, operational, and outcome dashboards.** Per-trial-and-per-cohort recruitment-funnel dashboards (entry, prescreen-completion, handoff-rate, consent-rate-from-handoff, randomized-rate-from-consent, by demographic stratum, by referral source, by channel), operational dashboards, and diversity-action-plan dashboards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon Comprehend Medical (optional) for medical-named-entity recognition over patient-reported text.** When the patient reports a medication name, a symptom, a diagnosis, or a related entity in conversation, Comprehend Medical can extract structured terms for matching against the eligibility-criterion rules.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon SageMaker (optional) for custom vulnerability-flag classifier hosting.** Where the institution has invested in a custom classifier for detecting vulnerability indicators (capacity concerns, coercion patterns, financial-vulnerability patterns), SageMaker provides the hosted-inference endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Architecture Diagram
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```mermaid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m flowchart LR
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     subgraph Channels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       WEB[Web Chat]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       APP[Institution Patient App]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       SMS[SMS via Pinpoint]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       VOICE[Voice via Connect]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       LANDING[Sponsor Recruitment<br/>Landing Page]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     end
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     subgraph Edge
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       WAF[AWS WAF]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       APIGW[API Gateway]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     end
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     subgraph Conversation_Core
